  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "HR Manager",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Lead and oversee the full spectrum of HR and administrative for office, including recruitment, compensation and benefits management, policy development, employee remuneration, and overall HR strategy.</p></li><li><p>Manage the HR teams with providing guidance, coaching, and support. </p></li><li><p>Collaborate with the Heads of Departments to develop and implement HR policies, strategies, and processes that attract, retain, and develop talent while enhancing workforce productivity.</p></li><li><p>Provide expert advice on employee relations matters to foster a cohesive, collaborative, and positive workplace culture.</p></li><li><p>Align HR strategies with business objectives and contribute as a key member of the management team to address organizational challenges.</p></li><li><p>Prepare and review employment-related documentation, including appointment letters, increment letters, resignation acceptance letters, and disciplinary action letters.</p></li><li><p>Manage payroll processing, benefits administration, reimbursements, CPF contributions, IR8A filings, and other statutory or government claims.</p></li><li><p>Conduct annual job grading, salary banding, and performance evaluations.</p></li><li><p>Assess training and development needs and make recommendations to enhance employee growth and organizational capability.</p></li><li><p>Oversee the management of insurance policies, including health, workers’ compensation, and liability insurance, and coordinate claims and renewals.</p></li><li><p>Plan and manage welfare initiatives, company events, and team-building activities.</p></li></ul><ul><li>Develop and implement programs to enhance talent acquisition, retention, and employee engagement.</li></ul><ul><li><p>Introduce initiatives to improve workforce productivity and operational efficiency.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Degree in Human Resources, Business Administration, or a related field.</p></li><li><p>Prefer 5 years of HR manager experience, within the engineering or construction sector.</p></li><li><p>Strong knowledge of HR laws and regulations, including work pass regulations and procedures in Singapore.</p></li><li><p>Excellent communication, interpersonal, and analytical skills.</p></li><li><p>Ability to handle sensitive and confidential matters with discretion and integrity.</p></li><li><p>Strong multitasking, planning, and coordination abilities with attention to detail.</p></li></ul>",
